body:
@kennknowles do you know much about our coveralls setup? I see we're reporting coverage from jenkins rather than travis. Coveralls [also supports travis](https://coveralls.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/201347419-Coveralls-currently-supports), and from what I can tell Travis has a couple advantages:
- Infers correct pull request context to [associate with coverage data](https://coveralls.io/builds/6931744).
- Also [runs on fork repositories](https://coveralls.io/builds/6932737) since the .travis.yml config is part of source.
